result.execSummary:
The defendant Dontay Rashad Reasby was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • False Imprisonment [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments, Use Dangerous Weapon (Felony 5+ Yrs)], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.30.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dontay Rashad Reasby in court with attorney Jerome J. Shimek.  Defendant Dontay Rashad Reasby in custody.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Sentencing proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant. 

As to Count 1:  The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 3 years, consecutive to any other sentence. The term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 18 months, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 18 months. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 3 years.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION
-Serve 60 days in HOC as Condition Time, STAYED pending review: agent to call court to schedule review 60 days after release.
-Batterers Intervention program.
-Parenting classes.
-Absolute sobriety.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with victim without approval of agent.
-3rd party contact for the purpose of time with children as approved by agent.
-Maintain/obtain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges to be paid during period of probation, if revoked to be paid from 25% of prison funds, balance paid during Extended Supervision, failure to pay results in a civil judgment. All NON-Mandatory court costs, fees and surcharges due to inability to pay.


*Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER.
*Court advised due to DV conviction under federal law the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession.
*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.

Filed: Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief, Memorandum of Conditions of Probation, Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement, Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence.

Defendant Dontay Rashad Reasby in court with attorney Jerome J. Shimek.  Defendant Dontay Rashad Reasby in custody.  Owen M. Piotrowski for Nicolas Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.

AS TO COUNTS 2 and 3:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders Counts 2 and 3 DISMISSED but read-in for sentencing purposes.  

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
The Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may may vote in any election until his civil rights are restored and may not possess a firearm.
